qas.question: In 1200, what area did the houses of Savoy, Zahringer, Habsburg, and Kyburg comprise?
In 1264 AD, what caused the Kyburg dynasty to fall?

answers.text: extinction of its male line in 1263

qas.question: Who claimed the Kyburg lands after their fall in 1264 AD?
Which Holy Roman Emperor were the Habsburgs under in 1273 AD?
What did the three regions of Uri, Schwyz, and Unterwalden become known as?

context: By 1200, <a0_0>the Swiss plateau<a0_0/> comprised the dominions of the houses of Savoy, Zähringer, Habsburg, and Kyburg. Some regions (Uri, Schwyz, Unterwalden, later known as <a4_0>Waldstätten<a4_0/>) were accorded the Imperial immediacy to grant the empire direct control over the mountain passes. With the <a1_0>extinction of its male line in 1263<a1_0/> the Kyburg dynasty fell in AD 1264; then <a2_0>the Habsburgs<a2_0/> under <a3_0>King Rudolph I<a3_0/> (Holy Roman Emperor in 1273) laid claim to the Kyburg lands and annexed them extending their territory to the eastern Swiss plateau.
